snippet: New restrictions will probably make the fish more expensive for consumers, but markets and fish-and-chip shops are unlikely to run low.
abstract: New restrictions on commercial cod fishing in Gulf of Maine, imposed by federal government in effort to restore fishery from record low, are likely to make fish more expensive for consumers.
lead_paragraph: New restrictions will probably make the fish more expensive for consumers, but markets and fish-and-chip shops are unlikely to run low.

headline.main: Restrictions May Affect Price of Cod From Maine
headline.print_headline: Restrictions May Affect Price of Cod From Maine
